{"can_edit": true, "from": {"id": "100003249072744", "name": "Sttbrn Infnty"}, "revision": "10154290919615019", "updated_time": "2014-05-30T11:50:11+0000", "can_delete": true, "created_time": "2014-05-30T11:50:11+0000", "message": "<p><span>Commands for Network Management<br /><br /> 1. To manage the different services:<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# chkconfig named on<br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# chkconfig httpd on<br /><br /> After configuring any service we use this command so that this service will automatically be active after rebooting the computer.<br /><br /> To deactivate the service:<span><br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# chkconfig named off<br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# chkconfig httpd off<br /><br /> 2. To start NIC:<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ifup eth0<br /><br />        To start Virtual NIC<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ifup eth0 : 0<br /><br />      To stop NIC<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ifdown eth0<br /><br />    To stop Virtual NIC<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ifdown eth0 : 0<br /><br /> 3. To see the configured IP address or NIC&#039;s information<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ifconfig<br /><br /> To reset the IP address in temporarily<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ifconfig eth0  netmask  up<br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ifconfig eth1  netmask  up<br /><br /> To reset the IP address for virtual NIC in temporarily<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ifconfig eth0 : 0  netmask  up<br /><br /> 4. To run setup wizard &amp; using wizard can be activated or deactivated<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# setup<br /><br /> 5. To test and troubleshoot The IP address<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ping 192.168.0.101<br /><br /> 6. To see the information of network connections<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# netstat<br /><br /> Commands for Routing Information:<br /><br /> 1. To see the present routing information of routing table<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# route \u2013 n<br /><br /> 2. To add new information in routing table<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# route add -net 192.168.100.80 netmask 255.255.255.248 gw 205.201.30.12<br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# route add -net 192.168.100.80 netmask 255.255.255.248 gateway1<br /><br /> 3. To delete routing information from the routing table<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# route del -net 192.168.100.80 netmask 255.255.255.248 gw 205.201.30.12<br /><br /> 4. To add default  routing information in routing table<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# route add default 192.168.1.1<br /><br /> 5. To delete default routing information from the routing table<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# route del default<br /><br /> 6. To test the physical and logical connectivity from host PC to destination PC<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# traceroute 192.168.0.101<br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# traceroute <a href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2F&amp;h=BAQFeDMM0&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fwww.google.com\\u00252F&amp;h=BAQFeDMM0&amp;s=1&quot;);\">www.google.com</a></a><br /><br /> Commands to connectify with other PC<br /><br /> 1. To login in a remote machine and to take full control<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# telnet 192.168.0.101<br /><br /> Another command to login in a remote machine and to take full control<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# ssh 192.168.0.101 <br /> This command is much secure and stronger than telnet.<br /><br /> 2. To copy files and directories in running computer from a remote computer<br /><br />     [root&#064;localhost malek]# scp 192.168.0.101 :  /etc/sysconfig/home</span></span></p><br />", "subject": "Commands for Network Management, Routing information and Connectify", "id": "10154290919620019", "icon": "https://fbstatic-a.akamaihd.net/rsrc.php/v2/y7/r/8zhNI-VGpiI.png"}